<% case @action.to_s %>
<% when 'endorse' %>
  The name <%= @name.name %> has been endorsed.
  
  What does this mean?
  ====================
  Our team of curators have marked this name and the associated metadata as
  suitable for validation. However, names are not valid (and do not have
  priority) until they have been published and the Registry is notified of
  publication.
  
  What to do next?
  ================
  If you are currently writing the manuscript that describes this taxon,
  undergoing peer-review, or the manuscript is currently in press, please
  remember to notify the SeqCode registry once the paper has been published.
  <% if @name.register %>
  If the paper has already been published and a DOI has been assigned, notify
  the SeqCode Registry at:
  <%= notify_register_url(@name.register) %>
  <% end %>
  To view the name's entry in the Registry, visit:
  <%= name_url(@name) %>
<% when 'return' %>
  The name <%= @name.name %> has been returned.

  What does this mean?
  ====================
  Our team of curators have found some issues with the name and have returned
  it to you for further inspection.

  What to do next?
  ================
  Review the correspondance with the curators to determine the following
  actions in the name page:
  <%= name_url(@name) %>
  <% if @name.register %>
  Additional information may also be available in the register list page:
  <%= register_url(@name.register) %>
  <% end %>
<% when 'validate' %>
  The name <%= @name.name %> has been validated.

  What does this mean?
  ====================
  The name is now considered valid under the SeqCode.

  What to do next?
  ================
  You can cite the name without quotation marks now. The formal recommended
  styling is: <%= @name.formal_txt %>
  <% if @name.register %>
  You can also cite the register list using the assigned DOI:
  <%= @name.register.doi_url %>
  (it may take a few days before the DOI is properly registered).
  <% end %>
<% when 'claim' %>
  You have claimed the name <%= @name.name %>

  What does this mean?
  ====================
  The data and metadata associated to this name are no longer publicly
  available, and you are now able to edit all the associated metadata.

  What to do next?
  ================
  You can now complete all the validation requirements and submit the name for
  endorsement. To see and edit the name data and metadata, visit:
  <%= name_url(@name) %>
<% when 'unclaim' %>
  You have unclaimed the name <%= @name.name %>
  or somebody else made this change for you.

  What does this mean?
  ====================
  You are no longer authorized to modify this name's data and metadata.

  What to do next?
  ================
  If you were aware and agree with this, you don't need to take any further
  actions. If you think this was a mistake, please contact us at:
  <%= page_connect_url %>
<% end %>
